<div id="review_1841219938" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1841219938" />
    <a title="Kent Winward" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1054712-kent-winward"><img alt="Kent Winward" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1408199296p2/1054712.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1841219938?book_show_action=true">Jan 01, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kent Winward" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kent Winward" href="/user/show/1054712-kent-winward">Kent Winward</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1841219938" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14475467697538823820">This is great for a historic look back at these philosophies. This was written almost one hundred years ago, so the implications of these different philosophies has changed over the years, but we need to know where we have been to figure out where we are going. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


